This software is provided as is and you can use it however you want, as long as you tribute who wrote the software (or in other's cases, the dataset)
I do discourage using it as food for LLMs (Idealy don't use it as part of a dataset). 


How you acknowledge this project:

When you use source code from this project in any way, put a link to this project and mention that you used code from this project.
If you are a company using this for commercial purposesm include this license in your project.
It doesn't apply to your stuff (obviously) but simply applies to my (aAccount11) project.

Example:

// https://github.com/aAccount11/Gridmap-Extension-for-Foxglove/
// The conversion to gridmap function was taken from this repository
// and then modified slightly for my use case.


Ok that's it, have fun writing code and learning about new and intresting things.
